.env

# ORM = Object relation mapping .
# pydantic = data validation and settings management using python type annotations.
# Alembic = database migrations for SQLAlchemy.
# user_controller = user controller for handling user-related operations.
# task_controller = task controller for handling task-related operations.
# task_service = task service for handling business logic related to tasks.
# user_service = user service for handling business logic related to users.
# main.py = main application file that initializes the FastAPI app and includes the routes for user and task operations.
#models.py = defines the database models for users and tasks using SQLAlchemy.
#schemas.py = defines the Pydantic models for request and response validation for users and tasks.
#database.py = sets up the database connection and session management using SQLAlchemy.
#SQLAlchemy = SQL toolkit and Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) library for Python. It provides a full suite of well-known enterprise-level persistence patterns, designed for efficient and high-performing database access. 
#SQLAlchemy allows developers to work with databases using Python objects and provides a powerful and flexible way to interact with databases.
#FastAPI = FastAPI is a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.6+ based on standard Python type hints. It is designed to be easy to use and to provide high performance, making it a great choice for building APIs quickly and efficiently. FastAPI also includes features such as automatic validation, serialization, and documentation generation, which can help developers build robust and well-documented APIs with minimal effort.